To align a row of divs to the right using flex in CSS, you can use the following code:

```css
.row {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}
```

This will align all the children elements of the .row class to the right. Here's an example:

HTML:

```html
<div class="row">
  <div>Div 1</div>
  <div>Div 2</div>
  <div>Div 3</div>
</div>
```

CSS:

```css
.row {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}
```

In this example, the .row class is set to display as a flex container and the justify-content property is set to flex-end, which aligns all the children elements to the right. You can add more divs inside the row div to test it out. I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.
